rlm-awsprofile

Pick an AWS profile interactively with fzf and export it as
AWS_PROFILE in the current shell.

Runs `aws configure list-profiles` to enumerate the profiles
configured in ~/.aws/credentials and ~/.aws/config, pipes them
into fzf, and exports the selection so subsequent aws / boto3 /
terraform / pulumi commands in this shell pick it up.

Aborting fzf (Esc / Ctrl-C) leaves AWS_PROFILE set to an empty
string. Re-run to choose a different profile.

Aliases: awsprofile
